techmeme.title: Alibaba's Qwen releases Qwen-Image, an AI image generation model focused on accurate text rendering, with support for alphabetic and logographic scripts (Carl Franzen/VentureBeat)
Super Micro reports Q4 revenue up 7.5% YoY to $5.76B, vs. $6.01B est., and lowers its fiscal year sales forecast; SMCI drops 14%+ after hours (Dina Bass/Bloomberg)
AMD reports Q2 revenue up 32% YoY to $7.7B vs. $7.43B est., Data Center revenue up 14% to $3.2B vs. $3.25B est., Client revenue up 67% to $2.5B vs. $2.56B est. (Ian King/Bloomberg)
Match Q2: revenue of $864M, flat YoY, net earnings of $125.5M, down from $133.3M YoY, and provides a Q3 forecast beating estimates; MTCH jumps 11% after hours (Natalie Lung/Bloomberg)
Filing: in its ChatGPT lawsuit, the NYT asked OpenAI to produce 120M user chats to analyze how often ChatGPT regurgitates its articles, after OpenAI offered 20M (Ashley Belanger/Ars Technica)
